PORT ELIZABETH - The bail hearing for a Nigerian pastor charged with human trafficking and sexual assault is set to continue Tuesday in the Port Elizabeth magistrate’s court. READ: Alleged sex-trafficking pastor in SA illegally The pastor, who is based in Durban, is alleged to have trafficked more than 30 girls and women who were from various branches of his church countrywide. He allegedly took the girls to a house in Umhlanga in KwaZulu-Natal where he sexually exploited them. African News Agency